@* Decision 130's BOUNDARY. An EventCallback [Parameter] is admitted only where a composing
   parent supplied one of its own methods for it -- that method is the entire emission. Here
   there is no parent, so there is nothing to call, and a listener wired to nothing renders
   correctly and then does nothing for the life of the page. Refused, not wired to a no-op. *@
<button id="b" @onclick="OnX">x</button>

@code {
    [Parameter] public EventCallback OnX { get; set; }
}
